article.description: J.T. Durley scored 21 points on 7-of-11 shooting to lead Wichita State past Southern Illinois 76-55 in the regular-season finale Saturday.
article.headline: Durley-led Wichita State improves to 17-0 at home with rout of SIU
article.linkText: SIU helps Wichita State to 17-0 record at home
article.story:
WICHITA, Kan. -- J.T. Durley scored 21 points on 7-of-11 shooting to lead Wichita State past Southern Illinois 76-55 in the regular-season finale Saturday.

Wichita State (23-8, 12-6 Missouri Valley) never trailed in improving to 17-0 at home. Clevin Hannah added 13 points for the Shockers, who will be the second seed in the conference tournament.

Southern Illinois (15-14, 6-12) was led by Kendal Brown-Surles' season-high 15 points. The Salukis are locked into ninth place and will face Drake in the tournament.

Wichita State took control two minutes into the second half. The Shockers went on a 22-7 run over 10 minutes, allowing only one Southern Illinois field goal, and led 62-39. Durley scored nine of Wichita State's points during the run.

Durley scored seven of Wichita State's final 11 points of the first half to give the Shockers a 38-26 advantage at intermission.
